{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DzRUMjrdXcUaTjgQ46oZUi","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I now have a complete understanding of the commitment algorithm. Here's the summary:\n\n## Fairness Package Structure\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/`\n\n**Files in src/**:\n- `commitment.ts` - Commitment computation and verification\n- `crash.ts` - Crash point calculation using HMAC-based randomness\n- `verification.ts` - Full round verification logic\n- `index.ts` - Public exports\n- Test files: `commitment.test.ts`, `crash.test.ts`, `verification.test.ts`\n\n---\n\n## Commitment Algorithm Breakdown\n\n### **1. Commitment Computation** (`commitmentment.ts`)\n```typescript\ncomputeCommitment(serverSeed: string): string\n  Input: serverSeed (hex string, e.g., 64-char hex = 32 bytes)\n  Process:\n    1. Convert hex string to bytes: hexToBytes(serverSeed)\n    2. Compute SHA256 hash of those bytes\n    3. Convert hash back to hex string: bytesToHex(hash)\n  Output: 64-character hex string (256-bit hash)\n  Library: @noble/hashes (v1.6.0)\n```\n\n**Verification**: `verifyCommitment(serverSeed, commitment)` — case-insensitive comparison of computed vs claimed commitment.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Crash Point Algorithm** (`crash.ts`)\n\nTwo-stage process:\n\n**Stage 1 — Deterministic Seed Hashing**:\n```typescript\ncomputeCrashPoint(serverSeed, publicSeed, roundId, gameId = \"crash\")\n  Input: \n    - serverSeed (hex string, 32 bytes)\n    - publicSeed (any string)\n    - roundId (any string)\n    - gameId (any string, defaults to \"crash\")\n  Process:\n    1. Convert serverSeed to bytes\n    2. Create message: `${publicSeed}:${roundId}:${gameId}` (UTF-8 string)\n    3. HMAC-SHA256(serverSeedBytes, messageBytes) \n       → Message Authentication Code (64 bytes)\n    4. Convert to hex: bytesToHex(hash) (128 chars)\n    5. Pass hex to hashToCrashPoint()\n  Output: Number >= 1.0 (typically 1.00 to 100+)\n```\n\n**Stage 2 — Hash-to-Crash Point Conversion**:\n```typescript\nhashToCrashPoint(hashHex: string): number\n  Input: 128-character hex hash string\n  Process:\n    1. Take first 13 hex chars (52 bits): parseInt(hashHex.substring(0, 13), 16)\n    2. Define e = 2^52 = 4503599627370496\n    3. Apply formula:\n       h = first 13 hex chars as integer\n       numerator = 100 * e - h\n       denominator = e - h\n       result = floor(numerator / denominator) / 100\n    4. Clamp to minimum 1.0: Math.max(1.0, result)\n  Output: Number >= 1.0\n  \n  Mathematical properties:\n    - ~50% of outcomes crash at or below 2.0x\n    - Expected value is balanced (no house bias)\n    - Uses only first 52 bits (leaves rest unused)\n```\n\n---\n\n### **3. Round Verification** (`verification.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nverifyRound(round: RoundData): VerificationResult\n  RoundData:\n    - roundId: string\n    - gameId: string\n    - serverSeed: string (hex)\n    - publicSeed: string\n    - commitment: string (hex)\n    - claimedOutcome: number\n    \n  Checks:\n    1. verifyCommitment(serverSeed, commitment) — must match\n    2. computeCrashPoint(serverSeed, publicSeed, roundId, gameId) \n       — computed outcome must match claimedOutcome ±0.01 tolerance\n       \n  Returns:\n    {\n      valid: boolean,\n      errors: string[],  // empty if valid\n      computedOutcome: number\n    }\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Implementation Details for Backend Replication\n\n1. **Hash Library**: Use `@noble/hashes` or equivalent SHA256/HMAC-SHA256 library\n2. **Input Format**: Server seed is **64-character hex string** (32 bytes)\n3. **HMAC Message Format**: `publicSeed:roundId:gameId` — colon-delimited, UTF-8 encoded\n4. **Crash Point Formula**: Uses first 13 hex chars of HMAC output (52-bit precision)\n5. **Tolerance**: Floating-point comparison allows ±0.01 difference\n6. **Case Handling**: Commitment verification is case-insensitive (normalizes to lowercase)\n\n---\n\n## Test Coverage\n- **Commitment**: Determinism, different seeds → different hashes, case-insensitivity\n- **Crash Point**: Always >= 1.0, determinism, gameId/roundId/seed variation, formula correctness\n- **Verification**: Valid rounds pass, commitment mismatches fail, outcome mismatches fail, floating-point tolerance works\n\nAll files are in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/` with full test coverage validating the exact algorithm you need to replicate."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad013778477ba787e (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 40278\ntool_uses: 15\nduration_ms: 51134</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6294e45f-f1b9-41ec-ad7c-8dacc5cf571a","uuid":"19b96e31-bb9f-4fda-a7b3-7df34bbf5943","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the full contents of `sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts` — I need to understand the commitment algorithm to replicate it in the backend. Also check what other files exist in `sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/`.","agentId":"ad013778477ba787e","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I now have a complete understanding of the commitment algorithm. Here's the summary:\n\n## Fairness Package Structure\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/`\n\n**Files in src/**:\n- `commitment.ts` - Commitment computation and verification\n- `crash.ts` - Crash point calculation using HMAC-based randomness\n- `verification.ts` - Full round verification logic\n- `index.ts` - Public exports\n- Test files: `commitment.test.ts`, `crash.test.ts`, `verification.test.ts`\n\n---\n\n## Commitment Algorithm Breakdown\n\n### **1. Commitment Computation** (`commitmentment.ts`)\n```typescript\ncomputeCommitment(serverSeed: string): string\n  Input: serverSeed (hex string, e.g., 64-char hex = 32 bytes)\n  Process:\n    1. Convert hex string to bytes: hexToBytes(serverSeed)\n    2. Compute SHA256 hash of those bytes\n    3. Convert hash back to hex string: bytesToHex(hash)\n  Output: 64-character hex string (256-bit hash)\n  Library: @noble/hashes (v1.6.0)\n```\n\n**Verification**: `verifyCommitment(serverSeed, commitment)` — case-insensitive comparison of computed vs claimed commitment.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Crash Point Algorithm** (`crash.ts`)\n\nTwo-stage process:\n\n**Stage 1 — Deterministic Seed Hashing**:\n```typescript\ncomputeCrashPoint(serverSeed, publicSeed, roundId, gameId = \"crash\")\n  Input: \n    - serverSeed (hex string, 32 bytes)\n    - publicSeed (any string)\n    - roundId (any string)\n    - gameId (any string, defaults to \"crash\")\n  Process:\n    1. Convert serverSeed to bytes\n    2. Create message: `${publicSeed}:${roundId}:${gameId}` (UTF-8 string)\n    3. HMAC-SHA256(serverSeedBytes, messageBytes) \n       → Message Authentication Code (64 bytes)\n    4. Convert to hex: bytesToHex(hash) (128 chars)\n    5. Pass hex to hashToCrashPoint()\n  Output: Number >= 1.0 (typically 1.00 to 100+)\n```\n\n**Stage 2 — Hash-to-Crash Point Conversion**:\n```typescript\nhashToCrashPoint(hashHex: string): number\n  Input: 128-character hex hash string\n  Process:\n    1. Take first 13 hex chars (52 bits): parseInt(hashHex.substring(0, 13), 16)\n    2. Define e = 2^52 = 4503599627370496\n    3. Apply formula:\n       h = first 13 hex chars as integer\n       numerator = 100 * e - h\n       denominator = e - h\n       result = floor(numerator / denominator) / 100\n    4. Clamp to minimum 1.0: Math.max(1.0, result)\n  Output: Number >= 1.0\n  \n  Mathematical properties:\n    - ~50% of outcomes crash at or below 2.0x\n    - Expected value is balanced (no house bias)\n    - Uses only first 52 bits (leaves rest unused)\n```\n\n---\n\n### **3. Round Verification** (`verification.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nverifyRound(round: RoundData): VerificationResult\n  RoundData:\n    - roundId: string\n    - gameId: string\n    - serverSeed: string (hex)\n    - publicSeed: string\n    - commitment: string (hex)\n    - claimedOutcome: number\n    \n  Checks:\n    1. verifyCommitment(serverSeed, commitment) — must match\n    2. computeCrashPoint(serverSeed, publicSeed, roundId, gameId) \n       — computed outcome must match claimedOutcome ±0.01 tolerance\n       \n  Returns:\n    {\n      valid: boolean,\n      errors: string[],  // empty if valid\n      computedOutcome: number\n    }\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Implementation Details for Backend Replication\n\n1. **Hash Library**: Use `@noble/hashes` or equivalent SHA256/HMAC-SHA256 library\n2. **Input Format**: Server seed is **64-character hex string** (32 bytes)\n3. **HMAC Message Format**: `publicSeed:roundId:gameId` — colon-delimited, UTF-8 encoded\n4. **Crash Point Formula**: Uses first 13 hex chars of HMAC output (52-bit precision)\n5. **Tolerance**: Floating-point comparison allows ±0.01 difference\n6. **Case Handling**: Commitment verification is case-insensitive (normalizes to lowercase)\n\n---\n\n## Test Coverage\n- **Commitment**: Determinism, different seeds → different hashes, case-insensitivity\n- **Crash Point**: Always >= 1.0, determinism, gameId/roundId/seed variation, formula correctness\n- **Verification**: Valid rounds pass, commitment mismatches fail, outcome mismatches fail, floating-point tolerance works\n\nAll files are in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/` with full test coverage validating the exact algorithm you need to replicate."}],"totalDurationMs":51134,"totalTokens":40278,"totalToolUseCount":15,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":469,"cache_read_input_tokens":38471,"output_tokens":1334,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":469},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
