{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014uMPHX4poLvicSgZd8TVoc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Architecture\n     2→\n     3→## Overview\n     4→\n     5→RNG Utopia is structured as a pnpm monorepo containing the platform shell, individual game applications, and shared packages. The frontend is built with React, TypeScript, and Vite. The backend consists of Solana programs for on-chain game logic and a lightweight off-chain service layer for real-time coordination.\n     6→\n     7→Scope alignment note: V1 direction is defined in `../../docs/SCOPE.md`. Architectural details for token, referral/rakeback, and other expansion mechanics are post-V1 unless explicitly called out as V1.\n     8→\n     9→**Core Principles:**\n    10→- On-chain programs are authoritative for all financial settlement\n    11→- Off-chain services handle UX optimization and real-time coordination\n    12→- All randomness is provably fair and independently verifiable\n    13→- Idempotent operations prevent double-settlement and replay attacks\n    14→\n    15→---\n    16→\n    17→## Monorepo Structure\n    18→\n    19→```\n    20→rng-utopia/\n    21→├── apps/\n    22→│   ├── platform/           # Main shell - routing, layout, shared state\n    23→│   ├── close-call/         # Pari-mutuel BTC candle prediction\n    24→│   ├── crash-simulator/    # P2P crash game - last to cash out wins\n    25→│   ├── lord-of-rngs/       # Winner-takes-all jackpot wheel\n    26→│   ├── coinflip/           # 1v1 50/50 coin flip\n    27→│   ├── game-of-trades/     # Multiplayer trading competition\n    28→│   ├── slots-utopia/       # P2P slots (loyalty-gated)\n    29→│   ├── chart-the-course/   # Price trajectory prediction\n    30→│   └── tug-of-earn/        # Team-based tap battle\n    31→├── packages/\n    32→│   ├── ui/                 # Design system components\n    33→│   ├── game-engine/        # Client-side game state (UI only, not authoritative)\n    34→│   ├── fairness/           # Provable fairness verification utilities\n    35→│   ├── wallet/             # Privy integration and transaction helpers\n    36→│   ├── vrf/                # VRF client integration\n    37→│   ├── price-feeds/        # Real-time price data integration\n    38→│   └── config/             # Shared configuration (eslint, tsconfig, etc.)\n    39→├── solana/                 # Solana programs (Anchor workspace)\n    40→│   ├── programs/coinflip/  # Coinflip game logic, settlement\n    41→│   ├── programs/platform/  # Platform settings, player profiles\n    42→│   └── shared/             # Common types, fee constants (lib crate)\n    43→├── crates/                 # Shared Rust libraries\n    44→│   ├── payout-math/        # Payout calculation invariants\n    45→│   └── fairness-core/      # Commit-reveal and verification logic\n    46→├── services/\n    47→│   ├── coordinator/        # Real-time game coordination (Node.js/Rust)\n    48→│   └── indexer/            # On-chain event indexing service\n    49→├── package.json\n    50→├── pnpm-workspace.yaml\n    51→├── turbo.json\n    52→└── README.md\n    53→```\n    54→\n    55→---\n    56→\n    57→## Custody Model\n    58→\n    59→**Architecture Decision: Non-Custodial (Recommended)**\n    60→\n    61→Players always move funds on-chain into per-round pool escrow PDAs. The platform never holds user balances in off-chain ledgers.\n    62→\n    63→### Why Non-Custodial\n    64→\n    65→| Aspect | Non-Custodial | Custodial |\n    66→|--------|---------------|-----------|\n    67→| Trust model | Trustless - funds in escrow PDAs | Requires trust in platform |\n    68→| Compliance | Simpler - not a money transmitter | Requires banking-grade ledgering |\n    69→| Transparency | Full on-chain auditability | Requires external audits |\n    70→| UX friction | More transactions | Faster micro-bets |\n    71→\n    72→### Fund Flow\n    73→\n    74→```\n    75→Entry:\n    76→1. Player clicks to join a round\n    77→2. Frontend constructs entry transaction:\n    78→   - Transfer SOL to round-specific escrow PDA\n    79→   - Register player in pool state\n    80→3. Transaction signed by player's wallet\n    81→4. Pool-manager program accepts entry atomically\n    82→5. Player's entry is now escrowed on-chain\n    83→\n    84→Payout:\n    85→1. Round resolves (outcome determined)\n    86→2. Settlement transaction executed:\n    87→   - Pool-manager calculates payouts\n    88→   - Fees transferred to treasury PDA\n    89→   - Winnings transferred directly to winner wallets\n    90→3. All transfers atomic in single transaction\n    91→```\n    92→\n    93→### UX Optimization (Without Custodial Balances)\n    94→\n    95→To reduce transaction friction while remaining non-custodial:\n    96→\n    97→- **Batched entries:** Allow multiple bets in single transaction where applicable\n    98→- **Session keys:** Privy session authority for faster signing (user-controlled delegation)\n    99→- **Transaction sponsorship:** Platform pays gas for small bets (relayer pattern)\n   100→- **Pre-approved limits:** User pre-authorizes max bet amounts per session\n   101→\n   102→---\n   103→\n   104→## Source of Truth\n   105→\n   106→| Data Type | Source of Truth | Why |\n   107→|-----------|-----------------|-----|\n   108→| User funds | On-chain (wallet + escrow PDAs) | Trustless custody |\n   109→| Pool state | On-chain (pool-manager PDAs) | Financial settlement |\n   110→| Round outcomes | On-chain (settlement tx) | Auditability |\n   111→| Fee collection | On-chain (treasury PDA) | Transparency |\n   112→| Game state (live) | Coordination server | Low latency |\n   113→| User profiles | Off-chain DB | Non-financial |\n   114→| Leaderboards | Indexer DB (derived) | Recomputable from chain |\n   115→| Round history | Indexer DB (derived) | Recomputable from chain |\n   116→\n   117→**Rule:** Anything involving money settlement must be on-chain. Derived views can be off-chain but must be recomputable from on-chain data.\n   118→\n   119→---\n   120→\n   121→## Provable Fairness Standard\n   122→\n   123→All games must use one of two approved randomness patterns. This is enforced via `packages/fairness` and `crates/fairness-core`.\n   124→\n   125→### Pattern 1: Commit-Reveal + Future Chain Seed\n   126→\n   127→**Use for:** Games with predetermined outcomes (Crash)\n   128→\n   129→```\n   130→Before betting opens:\n   131→1. Server generates serverSeed (random 32 bytes)\n   132→2. Server publishes commitment: commit = sha256(serverSeed)\n   133→3. Commitment stored on-chain or published via indexer\n   134→\n   135→During betting:\n   136→4. Players place bets (server cannot change serverSeed)\n   137→\n   138→At round start:\n   139→5. Capture publicSeed from future Solana slot blockhash\n   140→   (slot must be after betting closes)\n   141→\n   142→After round:\n   143→6. Server reveals serverSeed\n   144→7. Outcome computed: HMAC-SHA256(serverSeed, publicSeed || roundId || gameId)\n   145→8. Anyone can verify: sha256(serverSeed) == published commit\n   146→\n   147→Why this works:\n   148→- Server commits before knowing publicSeed → can't manipulate outcome\n   149→- publicSeed from future block → server can't predict it during betting\n   150→- Commitment public → server can't change serverSeed after betting\n   151→```\n   152→\n   153→**Implementation:**\n   154→```rust\n   155→// crates/fairness-core\n   156→pub fn compute_crash_point(\n   157→    server_seed: &[u8; 32],\n   158→    public_seed: &[u8; 32],\n   159→    round_id: u64,\n   160→    game_id: &str,\n   161→) -> f64 {\n   162→    let input = [public_seed, &round_id.to_le_bytes(), game_id.as_bytes()].concat();\n   163→    let hash = hmac_sha256(server_seed, &input);\n   164→    hash_to_crash_point(&hash)\n   165→}\n   166→\n   167→pub fn verify_commitment(server_seed: &[u8; 32], commitment: &[u8; 32]) -> bool {\n   168→    sha256(server_seed) == *commitment\n   169→}\n   170→```\n   171→\n   172→### Pattern 2: On-Chain VRF\n   173→\n   174→**Use for:** Games requiring on-chain winner selection (Lord of the RNGs, Coinflip)\n   175→\n   176→```\n   177→1. Round enters resolution phase\n   178→2. Program requests VRF (Switchboard/Orao)\n   179→3. VRF provider fulfills with proof\n   180→4. Program verifies proof and stores result\n   181→5. Winner selected using VRF output\n   182→6. Result permanently on-chain with proof\n   183→```\n   184→\n   185→**VRF Provider Requirements:**\n   186→- On-chain verifiability\n   187→- Low latency (sub-second for real-time games)\n   188→- Cost efficiency at scale\n   189→- Providers under evaluation: Switchboard VRF, Orao Network\n   190→\n   191→### Per-Game Fairness Requirements\n   192→\n   193→Each game spec must document:\n   194→- Which randomness pattern it uses\n   195→- When the outcome becomes determined\n   196→- What gets stored on-chain\n   197→- How a third party verifies the result\n   198→- Link to verification API/tool\n   199→\n   200→---\n   201→\n   202→## Event Ordering, Idempotency & Replay Protection\n   203→\n   204→### Round Arbiter\n   205→\n   206→Each game instance has a canonical Round Arbiter that:\n   207→- Issues monotonic sequence numbers (seqNo) for all events\n   208→- Maintains authoritative timestamps\n   209→- Resolves ordering disputes\n   210→\n   211→```typescript\n   212→interface RoundEvent {\n   213→  roundId: string;\n   214→  seqNo: number;           // Monotonic within round\n   215→  timestamp: number;       // Arbiter timestamp (ms)\n   216→  eventType: 'bet' | 'cashout' | 'settle' | ...;\n   217→  playerId: string;\n   218→  signature: string;       // Player's signature on payload\n   219→  payload: any;\n   220→}\n   221→```\n   222→\n   223→### Idempotency Requirements\n   224→\n   225→Every mutating action must be idempotent with deterministic IDs:\n   226→\n   227→```typescript\n   228→// Bet ID - deterministic, prevents double-betting\n   229→betId = hash(roundId, playerId, tier)\n   230→\n   231→// Settlement ID - one settlement per round\n   232→settlementId = roundId\n   233→\n   234→// Claim ID - one claim per player per round\n   235→claimId = hash(roundId, playerId)\n   236→```\n   237→\n   238→**On-chain enforcement:**\n   239→```rust\n   240→// pool-manager program\n   241→#[account]\n   242→pub struct PlayerEntry {\n   243→    pub round_id: u64,\n   244→    pub player: Pubkey,\n   245→    pub tier: u8,\n   246→    pub amount: u64,\n   247→    pub claimed: bool,  // Prevents double-claim\n   248→}\n   249→\n   250→// Entry instruction checks PDA doesn't exist (prevents double-bet)\n   251→// Claim instruction checks claimed == false, then sets to true\n   252→```\n   253→\n   254→### Replay Protection\n   255→\n   256→All signed requests must include:\n   257→- `nonce`: Unique per request (e.g., incrementing counter or UUID)\n   258→- `expiresAt`: Timestamp after which request is invalid\n   259→- Server validates signature + freshness before processing\n   260→\n   261→```typescript\n   262→interface SignedRequest {\n   263→  payload: any;\n   264→  nonce: string;\n   265→  expiresAt: number;\n   266→  signature: string;  // Sign(payload || nonce || expiresAt)\n   267→}\n   268→\n   269→// Server validation\n   270→function validateRequest(req: SignedRequest): boolean {\n   271→  if (Date.now() > req.expiresAt) return false;\n   272→  if (usedNonces.has(req.nonce)) return false;\n   273→  if (!verifySignature(req)) return false;\n   274→  usedNonces.add(req.nonce);  // With TTL cleanup\n   275→  return true;\n   276→}\n   277→```\n   278→\n   279→### Tie-Break Policy (Time-Sensitive Games)\n   280→\n   281→For games like Crash where timing determines winners:\n   282→\n   283→1. **Server authoritative:** Arbiter timestamp is final\n   284→2. **Sequence-based:** Within same millisecond, lower seqNo wins\n   285→3. **Deterministic:** Given same events, same winner every time\n   286→4. **No latency compensation:** Fairness through transparency, not adjustment\n   287→\n   288→---\n   289→\n   290→## Indexing & Data Availability\n   291→\n   292→### Indexer Service\n   293→\n   294→A dedicated indexer subscribes to on-chain events and builds queryable views:\n   295→\n   296→```\n   297→┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐\n   298→│   Solana    │────▶│   Indexer   │────▶│  Query DB   │\n   299→│  (Geyser)   │     │  Service    │     │ (Postgres)  │\n   300→└─────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘\n   301→                           │\n   302→                           ▼\n   303→                    ┌─────────────┐\n   304→                    │  Fast APIs  │\n   305→                    └─────────────┘\n   306→```\n   307→\n   308→**Data Sources:**\n   309→- Helius webhooks or Geyser plugin for program logs\n   310→- Account change subscriptions for pool states\n   311→\n   312→**Indexed Data:**\n   313→- Round history (all games)\n   314→- Player statistics\n   315→- Leaderboards\n   316→- Pool states (current and historical)\n   317→- Fee collection records\n   318→- Fairness verification data (commitments, reveals)\n   319→\n   320→**API Endpoints:**\n   321→```\n   322→GET /rounds/:gameId/:roundId\n   323→GET /rounds/:gameId?limit=50&offset=0\n   324→GET /players/:playerId/stats\n   325→GET /players/:playerId/history\n   326→GET /leaderboard/daily\n   327→GET /leaderboard/alltime\n   328→GET /pools/:gameId/current\n   329→GET /fees/transparency\n   330→GET /fairness/:roundId/verify\n   331→```\n   332→\n   333→### Source of Truth Rules\n   334→\n   335→| Query | Source | Reason |\n   336→|-------|--------|--------|\n   337→| \"What's my balance?\" | On-chain (RPC) | Financial |\n   338→| \"Did I win round X?\" | On-chain (RPC) | Financial |\n   339→| \"Show round history\" | Indexer DB | Performance |\n   340→| \"Show leaderboard\" | Indexer DB | Derived data |\n   341→| \"Verify round fairness\" | Indexer + on-chain | Verification |\n   342→\n   343→**Consistency guarantee:** Indexer DB is eventually consistent with on-chain. For financial queries, always verify against on-chain state.\n   344→\n   345→---\n   346→\n   347→## Operational Safety Controls\n   348→\n   349→### On-Chain Controls (pool-manager)\n   350→\n   351→```rust\n   352→#[account]\n   353→pub struct GameConfig {\n   354→    pub game_id: String,\n   355→    pub paused: bool,           // Emergency pause\n   356→    pub min_bet: u64,           // Minimum bet in lamports\n   357→    pub max_bet: u64,           // Maximum bet in lamports\n   358→    pub fee_bps: u16,           // Fee in basis points (max 1000 = 10%)\n   359→    pub allowed_tiers: [bool; 6], // Which tiers are active\n   360→    pub allowed_assets: Vec<Pubkey>, // Allowed token mints\n   361→    pub vrf_program_id: Pubkey, // Allowed VRF provider\n   362→    pub authority: Pubkey,      // Config update authority (multisig)\n   363→    pub version: u8,            // Config version for migrations\n   364→}\n   365→\n   366→// Instructions (all require multisig authority)\n   367→pub fn pause(ctx: Context<Pause>) -> Result<()>;\n   368→pub fn unpause(ctx: Context<Unpause>) -> Result<()>;\n   369→pub fn update_config(ctx: Context<UpdateConfig>, new_config: GameConfig) -> Result<()>;\n   370→pub fn emergency_refund(ctx: Context<EmergencyRefund>, round_id: u64) -> Result<()>;\n   371→```\n   372→\n   373→**Hard-coded limits (not configurable):**\n   374→- `MAX_FEE_BPS = 1000` (10% max fee, cannot be exceeded)\n   375→- `MAX_PLAYERS_PER_ROUND = 10000`\n   376→- `MAX_BET_LAMPORTS = 1_000_000_000_000` (1000 SOL absolute max)\n   377→\n   378→### Off-Chain Controls (Coordinator)\n   379→\n   380→**Rate Limiting:**\n   381→```typescript\n   382→const rateLimits = {\n   383→  perWallet: { window: '1m', max: 100 },  // 100 actions/minute/wallet\n   384→  perIP: { window: '1m', max: 500 },      // 500 actions/minute/IP\n   385→  perDevice: { window: '1m', max: 200 },  // 200 actions/minute/device\n   386→  global: { window: '1s', max: 10000 },   // 10k actions/second total\n   387→};\n   388→```\n   389→\n   390→**Anomaly Detection:**\n   391→- Unusually high join/cashout rate from single wallet\n   392→- Repeated failed transaction patterns\n   393→- Suspicious \"near-crash\" cashout clusters (potential bot signals)\n   394→- Circular referral patterns\n   395→- Rapid wallet creation + betting patterns\n   396→\n   397→**Circuit Breakers:**\n   398→- Auto-pause game if settlement failures exceed threshold\n   399→- Auto-pause if anomaly score exceeds threshold\n   400→- Alert on-call team for manual review\n   401→\n   402→**WAF Rules:**\n   403→- WebSocket connection limits per IP\n   404→- Message rate limiting per connection\n   405→- Payload size limits\n   406→- Invalid message pattern detection\n   407→\n   408→---\n   409→\n   410→## Shared Packages (Client-Side)\n   411→\n   412→### packages/game-engine\n   413→\n   414→**Important:** This package is for UI state management only. On-chain programs are authoritative for settlement.\n   415→\n   416→```typescript\n   417→// ALLOWED: UI state machines and prediction\n   418→class CrashGameState {\n   419→  phase: 'betting' | 'running' | 'crashed' | 'reveal';\n   420→  multiplier: number;  // Client-predicted, cosmetic only\n   421→\n   422→  // For display purposes - not used for settlement\n   423→  predictMultiplier(elapsedMs: number): number;\n   424→}\n   425→\n   426→// ALLOWED: Helpers for constructing instructions\n   427→function buildEntryInstruction(params: EntryParams): TransactionInstruction;\n   428→function buildCashoutInstruction(params: CashoutParams): TransactionInstruction;\n   429→\n   430→// ALLOWED: Verification utilities (read-only)\n   431→function verifyRoundOutcome(round: Round, serverSeed: string): boolean;\n   432→\n   433→// NOT ALLOWED: Settlement logic\n   434→// All payout calculations happen on-chain in pool-manager program\n   435→```\n   436→\n   437→**Rule:** `packages/game-engine` may never be the source of truth for payouts. It's validated against on-chain results, never the reverse.\n   438→\n   439→### packages/fairness\n   440→\n   441→Client-side verification utilities:\n   442→```typescript\n   443→// Verify commit-reveal\n   444→function verifyCommitment(serverSeed: string, commitment: string): boolean;\n   445→\n   446→// Compute expected crash point (for verification)\n   447→function computeCrashPoint(serverSeed: string, publicSeed: string, roundId: string): number;\n   448→\n   449→// Verify VRF proof (wrapper around on-chain verification)\n   450→function verifyVrfProof(proof: VrfProof, result: Uint8Array): boolean;\n   451→\n   452→// Full round verification\n   453→function verifyRound(round: RoundData): VerificationResult;\n   454→```\n   455→\n   456→### packages/ui\n   457→\n   458→Reusable components following a consistent design system:\n   459→- Core: Buttons, inputs, modals, cards\n   460→- Charts: Candlestick charts (Close Call), multiplier displays (Crash)\n   461→- Game primitives: Countdown timers, tier selection grids, bet input controls (1/2, x2, MAX), leaderboards\n   462→- Animations: Wheel spin (Lord of the RNGs), coin flip (Coinflip), crash visuals\n   463→- Feedback: Win/loss overlays, confetti, payout displays\n   464→\n   465→### packages/wallet\n   466→\n   467→Privy integration layer:\n   468→- Wallet connection and disconnection\n   469→- Transaction signing\n   470→- Balance queries\n   471→- Session key management\n   472→\n   473→### packages/price-feeds\n   474→\n   475→Real-time price data:\n   476→- WebSocket connections to price providers\n   477→- Pyth Network integration for on-chain price verification\n   478→- BTC/USD feed for Close Call (1-minute candle data)\n   479→- Candle boundary synchronization (open, high, low, close)\n   480→\n   481→---\n   482→\n   483→## Shared Rust Crates (On-Chain)\n   484→\n   485→### crates/payout-math\n   486→\n   487→Shared payout calculation logic used by pool-manager:\n   488→```rust\n   489→/// Calculate pari-mutuel payouts\n   490→pub fn calculate_parimutuel_payout(\n   491→    player_bet: u64,\n   492→    winning_pool: u64,\n   493→    total_pool: u64,\n   494→    fee_bps: u16,\n   495→) -> u64;\n   496→\n   497→/// Calculate winner-takes-all payout\n   498→pub fn calculate_winner_payout(\n   499→    total_pool: u64,\n   500→    fee_bps: u16,\n   501→) -> u64;\n   502→\n   503→/// Invariant: total_payouts + fees == total_pool\n   504→pub fn verify_payout_invariant(\n   505→    payouts: &[u64],\n   506→    fees: u64,\n   507→    total_pool: u64,\n   508→) -> bool;\n   509→```\n   510→\n   511→### crates/fairness-core\n   512→\n   513→Commit-reveal and verification logic:\n   514→```rust\n   515→pub fn compute_crash_point(...) -> f64;\n   516→pub fn verify_commitment(...) -> bool;\n   517→pub fn hash_to_crash_point(hash: &[u8; 32]) -> f64;\n   518→```\n   519→\n   520→---\n   521→\n   522→## Timing & Fairness Policy\n   523→\n   524→### Authoritative Timestamps\n   525→\n   526→- **Server is authoritative:** Arbiter timestamp determines action ordering\n   527→- **No latency compensation:** All players subject to same rules\n   528→- **Transparency over adjustment:** Publish RTT stats, don't try to \"fix\" latency\n   529→\n   530→### Time-Sensitive Game Rules\n   531→\n   532→**Crash (cashout timing):**\n   533→- Cashout accepted if arbiter receives request before `crashAt` timestamp\n   534→- If multiple cashouts at same multiplier, all are valid (all win their cashout amount, highest wins pool)\n   535→- Client multiplier display is cosmetic; server multiplier is authoritative\n   536→\n   537→**Close Call (bet timing):**\n   538→- Bet accepted if arbiter receives request before minute boundary\n   539→- Late bets rejected with clear error message\n   540→\n   541→### Fairness FAQ (User-Facing)\n   542→\n   543→Publish a fairness page explaining:\n   544→- How randomness is generated\n   545→- How to verify any round\n   546→- How timing is handled\n   547→- What the platform can and cannot manipulate\n   548→\n   549→---\n   550→\n   551→## Rewards Distribution (Deferred: Post-V1)\n   552→\n   553→### Fee Allocation Flow (Post-V1 Draft)\n   554→\n   555→```\n   556→Round Settlement\n   557→       │\n   558→       ▼\n   559→┌──────────────────┐\n   560→│  Total Pool      │\n   561→│  (all entries)   │\n   562→└────────┬─────────┘\n   563→         │\n   564→         ├── 97% → Winners\n   565→         │\n   566→         └── 3% Fee ─┬── 2.0% → Treasury PDA (platform revenue)\n   567→                     ├── 0.7% → Rakeback Pool PDA (raid boss rewards)\n   568→                     └── 0.3% → Chest Treasury PDA\n   569→```\n   570→\n   571→### Rakeback Distribution (Deferred: Post-V1)\n   572→\n   573→**Accumulation (On-Chain):**\n   574→- Each settlement deposits 0.7% of fees to Rakeback Pool PDA\n   575→- Pool accumulates throughout the day\n   576→\n   577→**Distribution (Daily, Off-Chain Triggered):**\n   578→```\n   579→1. At 00:00 UTC, snapshot leaderboard from indexer\n   580→2. Calculate each player's share: (player_points / total_points) × pool\n   581→3. Execute distribution transaction (batched if needed)\n   582→4. Clear daily points, reset pool\n   583→```\n   584→\n   585→**Anti-Double-Credit:**\n   586→- Distribution transaction includes `distribution_id = date_string`\n   587→- PDA tracks last distribution ID\n   588→- Instruction fails if already distributed for this period\n   589→\n   590→### Referral Distribution (Deferred: Post-V1)\n   591→\n   592→**Accumulation:**\n   593→- 0.3% of fees allocated per round\n   594→- Tracked per referee in off-chain DB (for performance)\n   595→- Periodically reconciled to on-chain\n   596→\n   597→**Distribution:**\n   598→- Real-time: Credit to off-chain balance, claimable on-chain\n   599→- Claim instruction transfers from Referral Pool PDA to user wallet\n   600→- Claim record prevents double-claim\n   601→\n   602→**Anti-Sybil:**\n   603→- Minimum wagering threshold before referral rewards activate\n   604→- Self-referral detection (same device/IP patterns)\n   605→- Suspicious pattern flagging for manual review\n   606→- KYC requirement for large referral payouts (threshold TBD)\n   607→\n   608→---\n   609→\n   610→## On-Chain Architecture\n   611→\n   612→### Solana Programs\n   613→\n   614→**pool-manager**\n   615→Manages the lifecycle of game pools:\n   616→- Create pool for a game round (PDA keyed by game type, tier, round ID)\n   617→- Accept player entries with idempotent bet IDs\n   618→- Lock pool when round starts\n   619→- Distribute winnings based on game outcome\n   620→- Handle refunds for cancelled/void rounds\n   621→- Prize pool carryover for rounds with no winner\n   622→- Single-claim enforcement via `claimed` flag\n   623→\n   624→**vrf-consumer**\n   625→Integrates with on-chain VRF provider:\n   626→- Request randomness for a specific round\n   627→- Store and verify VRF proofs\n   628→- Emit events when randomness is fulfilled\n   629→\n   630→**game-config**\n   631→Per-game configuration and controls:\n   632→- Pause/unpause functionality\n   633→- Configurable limits (min/max bet, fee bounds)\n   634→- Allowed assets and VRF providers\n   635→- Version tracking for migrations\n   636→\n   637→### Account Structure\n   638→\n   639→```\n   640→Pool PDA: seeds = [game_id, tier, round_id]\n   641→├── state: PoolState (betting, locked, settled)\n   642→├── total_entries: u64\n   643→├── green_pool / red_pool (Close Call)\n   644→├── entries: Vec<PlayerEntry>\n   645→├── outcome: Option<Outcome>\n   646→├── settlement_tx: Option<Signature>\n   647→└── carryover_from: Option<u64>  // Previous round ID if carryover\n   648→\n   649→PlayerEntry PDA: seeds = [round_id, player_pubkey, tier]\n   650→├── amount: u64\n   651→├── side: Option<Side>  // For Close Call\n   652→├── cashout_multiplier: Option<u64>  // For Crash\n   653→├── claimed: bool\n   654→└── payout: Option<u64>\n   655→\n   656→GameConfig PDA: seeds = [game_id]\n   657→├── paused: bool\n   658→├── min_bet: u64\n   659→├── max_bet: u64\n   660→├── fee_bps: u16\n   661→├── version: u8\n   662→└── authority: Pubkey\n   663→\n   664→Treasury PDA: seeds = [\"treasury\"]\n   665→├── total_collected: u64\n   666→└── withdrawal_authority: Pubkey (multisig)\n   667→```\n   668→\n   669→### Price Feeds\n   670→\n   671→Games requiring live prices use Pyth Network:\n   672→- Frontend subscribes to Pyth price feeds via WebSocket\n   673→- Game displays real-time prices to players\n   674→- At round resolution, program reads Pyth price account\n   675→- Price attestation ensures consistency between displayed and settled prices\n   676→\n   677→---\n   678→\n   679→## Real-Time Infrastructure\n   680→\n   681→### Coordination Server\n   682→\n   683→For multiplayer games, a coordination server maintains authoritative game state:\n   684→- Accepts player actions with signature verification\n   685→- Issues monotonic sequence numbers\n   686→- Broadcasts state updates to all participants\n   687→- Triggers on-chain settlement at round end\n   688→- Maintains Round Arbiter for each active round\n   689→\n   690→### WebSocket Protocol\n   691→\n   692→```typescript\n   693→// Client → Server\n   694→interface ClientMessage {\n   695→  type: 'join' | 'bet' | 'cashout' | 'subscribe';\n   696→  payload: any;\n   697→  nonce: string;\n   698→  expiresAt: number;\n   699→  signature: string;\n   700→}\n   701→\n   702→// Server → Client\n   703→interface ServerMessage {\n   704→  type: 'state' | 'event' | 'error' | 'ack';\n   705→  seqNo: number;\n   706→  timestamp: number;\n   707→  payload: any;\n   708→}\n   709→```\n   710→\n   711→### Game-Specific Requirements\n   712→\n   713→**Close Call**\n   714→- 1-minute candle synchronization with Pyth Network\n   715→- Round aligned to minute boundaries\n   716→- Betting open for full 60 seconds, locks at boundary\n   717→\n   718→**Crypto Crash Simulator**\n   719→- Continuous multiplier updates (60fps visual target)\n   720→- Per-tier state isolation\n   721→- Cash-out event ordering via arbiter seqNo\n   722→- Prize pool carryover tracking\n   723→\n   724→**Lord of the RNGs**\n   725→- Entry tracking with wheel visualization\n   726→- Phase transitions: Waiting → Countdown (60s) → Spin\n   727→- VRF request on countdown completion\n   728→\n   729→**Coinflip**\n   730→- Lobby creation and 1v1 matchmaking\n   731→- VRF request on match start\n   732→- Phase transitions: Create/Join → Flip (3s) → Resolution (2s)\n   733→\n   734→### Latency Targets\n   735→\n   736→| Operation | Target | Notes |\n   737→|-----------|--------|-------|\n   738→| UI responsiveness | < 100ms | Client-side |\n   739→| Price feed updates | < 500ms | WebSocket |\n   740→| Game state sync | < 200ms | WebSocket broadcast |\n   741→| On-chain settlement | ~400ms | Solana block time |\n   742→\n   743→---\n   744→\n   745→## Testing Strategy\n   746→\n   747→### On-Chain Program Tests\n   748→\n   749→**Invariant Tests:**\n   750→```rust\n   751→#[test]\n   752→fn test_payout_invariant() {\n   753→    // total_payouts + fees == total_pool (always)\n   754→}\n   755→\n   756→#[test]\n   757→fn test_cannot_pay_more_than_pool() {\n   758→    // Sum of all payouts <= pool - fees (always)\n   759→}\n   760→\n   761→#[test]\n   762→fn test_fee_within_bounds() {\n   763→    // fee_bps <= MAX_FEE_BPS (always)\n   764→}\n   765→\n   766→#[test]\n   767→fn test_single_claim() {\n   768→    // Second claim attempt fails\n   769→}\n   770→\n   771→#[test]\n   772→fn test_single_settlement() {\n   773→    // Second settlement attempt fails\n   774→}\n   775→```\n   776→\n   777→**Fairness Tests:**\n   778→```rust\n   779→#[test]\n   780→fn test_commitment_verification() {\n   781→    // sha256(server_seed) == commitment\n   782→}\n   783→\n   784→#[test]\n   785→fn test_crash_point_deterministic() {\n   786→    // Same inputs → same crash point (always)\n   787→}\n   788→\n   789→#[test]\n   790→fn test_vrf_proof_verification() {\n   791→    // Invalid proof rejected\n   792→}\n   793→```\n   794→\n   795→**Compute & Scale Tests:**\n   796→```rust\n   797→#[test]\n   798→fn test_max_players_compute() {\n   799→    // Settlement with MAX_PLAYERS_PER_ROUND doesn't exceed compute\n   800→}\n   801→\n   802→#[test]\n   803→fn test_worst_case_distribution() {\n   804→    // Payout to all players (everyone wins scenario)\n   805→}\n   806→```\n   807→\n   808→**Adversarial Tests:**\n   809→```rust\n   810→#[test]\n   811→fn test_double_entry_fails() {\n   812→    // Same player, same round, same tier → error\n   813→}\n   814→\n   815→#[test]\n   816→fn test_late_entry_fails() {\n   817→    // Entry after round locked → error\n   818→}\n   819→\n   820→#[test]\n   821→fn test_unauthorized_settlement_fails() {\n   822→    // Settlement without proper authority → error\n   823→}\n   824→\n   825→#[test]\n   826→fn test_overflow_protection() {\n   827→    // Large bet amounts don't cause overflow\n   828→}\n   829→```\n   830→\n   831→### Off-Chain Tests\n   832→\n   833→**Load Tests:**\n   834→- 5k concurrent WebSocket connections\n   835→- 1k actions/second sustained\n   836→- Measure latency percentiles (p50, p95, p99)\n   837→\n   838→**Chaos Tests:**\n   839→- Network partition recovery\n   840→- Coordinator restart during active round\n   841→- RPC provider failover\n   842→\n   843→**Integration Tests:**\n   844→- Full round lifecycle (bet → settle → claim)\n   845→- Fairness verification end-to-end\n   846→- Indexer consistency with on-chain state\n   847→\n   848→---\n   849→\n   850→## Program Upgrade Strategy\n   851→\n   852→### Versioning Scheme\n   853→\n   854→Each program maintains a version in its config PDA:\n   855→```rust\n   856→#[account]\n   857→pub struct ProgramConfig {\n   858→    pub version: u8,\n   859→    pub min_compatible_client: u8,\n   860→    // ...\n   861→}\n   862→```\n   863→\n   864→Frontend reads config PDA on load and warns if incompatible.\n   865→\n   866→### Upgrade Options\n   867→\n   868→**Option A: Upgrade in Place**\n   869→- Use Anchor's upgrade authority (multisig-controlled)\n   870→- Same program ID, new code\n   871→- Suitable for bug fixes, minor changes\n   872→\n   873→**Option B: Deploy New Program ID**\n   874→- New program with new ID\n   875→- Migrate users via frontend routing\n   876→- Suitable for breaking changes\n   877→\n   878→### Migration Playbook\n   879→\n   880→1. **Pre-migration:**\n   881→   - Announce maintenance window\n   882→   - Pause new round creation\n   883→   - Wait for active rounds to settle\n   884→\n   885→2. **Migration:**\n   886→   - Deploy new program (or upgrade)\n   887→   - Update frontend to point to new program\n   888→   - Update indexer subscriptions\n   889→\n   890→3. **Post-migration:**\n   891→   - Verify settlement works on new program\n   892→   - Resume round creation\n   893→   - Monitor for issues\n   894→\n   895→### Handling Active Pools During Upgrade\n   896→\n   897→- Never upgrade while rounds are unsettled\n   898→- If emergency upgrade needed:\n   899→  1. Pause new entries\n   900→  2. Fast-track settlement of active rounds\n   901→  3. Emergency refund if settlement impossible\n   902→  4. Then upgrade\n   903→\n   904→---\n   905→\n   906→## Security Considerations\n   907→\n   908→### Smart Contract Security\n   909→\n   910→- All programs audited before mainnet deployment\n   911→- Formal verification for critical payout logic (under consideration)\n   912→- Upgrade authority controlled by multisig (3-of-5 minimum)\n   913→- Bug bounty program for critical vulnerabilities\n   914→\n   915→### Frontend Security\n   916→\n   917→- No private keys stored in frontend\n   918→- All sensitive operations require wallet signature\n   919→- Input validation on all user-provided data\n   920→- CSP headers to prevent XSS\n   921→\n   922→### Operational Security\n   923→\n   924→- Admin operations require multisig approval\n   925→- Monitoring and alerting for anomalous activity\n   926→- Rate limiting on RPC and WebSocket connections\n   927→- Incident response playbook documented\n   928→\n   929→---\n   930→\n   931→## Environment Configuration\n   932→\n   933→### Development\n   934→- Local Solana validator\n   935→- Mock price feeds for deterministic testing\n   936→- Fast block times for rapid iteration\n   937→\n   938→### Staging\n   939→- Devnet deployment\n   940→- Real price feeds\n   941→- Reduced entry minimums for testing\n   942→- Full monitoring stack\n   943→\n   944→### Production\n   945→- Mainnet-beta deployment\n   946→- Real price feeds\n   947→- Full fee structure\n   948→- 24/7 monitoring and on-call rotation\n   949→\n   950→---\n   951→\n   952→## Dependencies\n   953→\n   954→### Frontend\n   955→- React 18+\n   956→- TypeScript 5+\n   957→- Vite 5+\n   958→- @solana/web3.js\n   959→- @privy-io/react-auth\n   960→- @pythnetwork/client\n   961→\n   962→### On-chain\n   963→- Anchor framework\n   964→- Solana 1.18+ (or current stable)\n   965→- VRF provider SDK (Switchboard or Orao)\n   966→\n   967→### Infrastructure\n   968→- RPC provider (Helius, Triton, or similar)\n   969→- WebSocket infrastructure (custom or managed)\n   970→- PostgreSQL for indexer\n   971→- Redis for rate limiting and caching\n   972→- Monitoring (Datadog, Grafana, or similar)\n   973→\n   974→---\n   975→\n   976→## Technical Research Notes\n   977→\n   978→### Open Items Requiring Further Research\n   979→\n   980→1. **VRF Provider Selection**\n   981→   - Switchboard vs Orao: latency, cost, reliability comparison\n   982→   - Custom VRF implementation feasibility\n   983→\n   984→2. **Indexer Architecture**\n   985→   - Helius webhooks vs custom Geyser plugin\n   986→   - Database choice: Postgres vs ClickHouse for analytics\n   987→\n   988→3. **Session Key Implementation**\n   989→   - Privy session authority patterns\n   990→   - Security implications of delegation\n   991→\n   992→4. **Cross-Region Fairness**\n   993→   - Geographic distribution of coordination servers\n   994→   - Latency measurement and transparency\n   995→\n   996→5. **Scale Testing**\n   997→   - Maximum concurrent players per tier\n   998→   - Compute limits for large payouts\n   999→   - WebSocket connection limits"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015m548nr74GxinrmjpE2Zbe","session_id":"6294e45f-f1b9-41ec-ad7c-8dacc5cf571a","uuid":"a60d4809-aaa9-403a-96cd-c24cd043e153"}
