{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015m548nr74GxinrmjpE2Zbe","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me compile my findings into a clear report.\n\n---\n\n## Monorepo Structure Exploration Report\n\nBased on my thorough investigation of the RNG Utopia monorepo, here are the detailed findings for scaffolding a new `services/backend/` package:\n\n### 1. **Workspace Configuration**\n\n**Root `pnpm-workspace.yaml`** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/pnpm-workspace.yaml`):\n- Workspace patterns are already defined:\n  ```yaml\n  packages:\n    - \"apps/*\"\n    - \"packages/*\"\n    - \"services/*\"\n  ```\n- The `services/` directory is **declared but does not yet exist** as a physical directory\n- It follows the same pattern as `apps/` and `packages/`\n\n**Root `package.json`** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/package.json`):\n- Uses `pnpm@9.15.0` as the package manager\n- Monorepo scripts delegate to Turbo:\n  - `pnpm dev` → `turbo run dev`\n  - `pnpm build:all` → `turbo run build`\n  - `pnpm lint` → `turbo run lint`\n  - `pnpm typecheck` → `turbo run typecheck`\n  - `pnpm test` → `turbo run test`\n- Workspace references available: `pnpm --filter @rng-utopia/<package>`\n\n### 2. **Build Pipeline (Turbo)**\n\n**`turbo.json`** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/turbo.json`):\n```json\n{\n  \"tasks\": {\n    \"build\": {\n      \"dependsOn\": [\"^build\"],\n      \"inputs\": [\"$TURBO_DEFAULT$\", \".env*\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"dist/**\", \".next/**\"]\n    },\n    \"dev\": {\n      \"cache\": false,\n      \"persistent\": true\n    },\n    \"lint\": {\n      \"dependsOn\": [\"^build\"],\n      \"inputs\": [\"$TURBO_DEFAULT$\", \".eslintrc*\"]\n    },\n    \"typecheck\": {\n      \"dependsOn\": [\"^build\"]\n    },\n    \"test\": {\n      \"dependsOn\": [\"^build\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n- All build tasks depend on `^build` (upstream dependencies must build first)\n- Lint, typecheck, and test depend on build\n- `dev` runs with no cache and is persistent (good for servers)\n\n### 3. **TypeScript Configuration Hierarchy**\n\n**Base config** (`packages/config/tsconfig.base.json`):\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"lib\": [\"ES2022\"],\n    \"module\": \"ESNext\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"bundler\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Node-specific variant** (`packages/config/tsconfig.node.json`):\n```json\n{\n  \"extends\": \"./tsconfig.base.json\",\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"composite\": true,\n    \"lib\": [\"ES2022\"],\n    \"module\": \"ESNext\",\n    \"outDir\": \"dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"src\"\n  }\n}\n```\n- This is the **template for Node.js backend services**\n- Has `outDir: dist` and `rootDir: src` pre-configured\n- Uses `composite: true` for Turbo integration\n\n### 4. **Package Naming & Structure Conventions**\n\nAll packages follow the `@rng-utopia/<name>` scope:\n\n**Example: `packages/fairness/package.json`**:\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"@rng-utopia/fairness\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"main\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n  \"types\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n  \"exports\": {\n    \".\": \"./src/index.ts\"\n  },\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"lint\": \"eslint .\",\n    \"lint:fix\": \"eslint . --fix\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest --passWithNoTests\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@noble/hashes\": \"^1.6.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@rng-utopia/config\": \"workspace:*\",\n    \"@types/node\": \"^22.10.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.7.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- Name: `@rng-utopia/<service-name>` (e.g., `@rng-utopia/coordinator`, `@rng-utopia/indexer`)\n- `\"private\": true` (monorepo internal use only)\n- `\"type\": \"module\"` (ESM)\n- `\"main\"` points directly to source (`./src/index.ts`, no build step)\n- `\"exports\"` field with main entry point\n- `@rng-utopia/config` as dev dependency for ESLint + TSConfig\n- No build tool needed—TypeScript source published directly (for lib packages)\n\n### 5. **Script Conventions**\n\nAll packages standardize on:\n```json\n{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"lint\": \"eslint .\",\n    \"lint:fix\": \"eslint . --fix\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest --passWithNoTests\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nFor **Node.js services** (backends), you may need:\n```json\n{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"dev\": \"node --loader tsx src/index.ts\",\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"start\": \"node dist/index.js\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint .\",\n    \"lint:fix\": \"eslint . --fix\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 6. **ESLint Configuration**\n\n**Pattern**: Use shared config from `@rng-utopia/config`:\n- `packages/config/eslint.config.js` exports three configs:\n  - `baseConfig` — for all TS projects\n  - `reactConfig` — extends baseConfig for React\n  - `nodeConfig` — extends baseConfig for Node.js servers\n- Projects consume via:\n  ```javascript\n  import { nodeConfig } from \"@rng-utopia/config/eslint.config.js\";\n  export default nodeConfig;\n  ```\n\n### 7. **Prettier Configuration**\n\n**Root `.prettierrc`** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/.prettierrc`):\n```json\n{\n  \"semi\": true,\n  \"singleQuote\": false,\n  \"tabWidth\": 2,\n  \"trailingComma\": \"es5\",\n  \"printWidth\": 100\n}\n```\n- Single `.prettierrc` at monorepo root applies to all packages\n- No per-package overrides\n\n### 8. **Directory Structure Summary**\n\nBased on ARCHITECTURE.md and actual package layout:\n\n```\nservices/\n├── coordinator/                # Real-time game coordination (Node.js service)\n│   ├── src/\n│   ├── package.json\n│   ├── tsconfig.json\n│   └── eslint.config.js\n├── indexer/                    # On-chain event indexing service\n│   ├── src/\n│   ├── package.json\n│   ├── tsconfig.json\n│   └── eslint.config.js\n└── backend/                    # NEW - Your backend service (generic name)\n    ├── src/\n    ├── package.json\n    ├── tsconfig.json\n    └── eslint.config.js\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Template: `services/backend/package.json`**\n\nBased on the patterns above, your new backend package should use:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"@rng-utopia/backend\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"main\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n  \"types\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n  \"exports\": {\n    \".\": \"./src/index.ts\"\n  },\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"dev\": \"node --loader tsx src/index.ts\",\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"start\": \"node dist/index.js\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint .\",\n    \"lint:fix\": \"eslint . --fix\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@solana/web3.js\": \"^1.98.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@rng-utopia/config\": \"workspace:*\",\n    \"@types/node\": \"^22.10.0\",\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.7.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.7.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Template: `services/backend/tsconfig.json`**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"extends\": \"@rng-utopia/config/tsconfig.node.json\",\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"types\": [\"node\"]\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src\"]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Template: `services/backend/eslint.config.js`**\n\n```javascript\nimport { nodeConfig } from \"@rng-utopia/config/eslint.config.js\";\n\nexport default nodeConfig;\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Key Takeaways for `services/backend/` Scaffolding**\n\n1. **Package Name**: Use `@rng-utopia/backend` (or choose a more specific name if it has a dedicated role)\n2. **Build Output**: Use `tsc` to transpile to `dist/`, source published as `.ts`\n3. **No Build Tool Like tsup**: Packages use raw TypeScript compilation + direct source 